Rethink scripting CLI API, allowing for more fine-grained control

Split `aab build` up into three new scriptable CLI commands,
`create_dist`, `build_dist`, and `package_dist`.
These are meant to be run in succession in more complex external
build scripts, allowing the latter to perform additional processing
steps at  key points in the add-on build process.
Bump version

Introduce fine-grained control over package conflict resolution

Allows tweaking directionality of self-conflict handling, which can
be desirable to avert specific scenarios in which Anki's conflict
resolution system can lead to both package versions being disabled

This is a quick hack to provide compatibility with building add-ons for Qt6 versions of Anki. A proper fix that creates Qt forms that are cross Qt5/Qt6 compatible will soon land in the develop branch.

Add full Qt6 support

By default aab will now compile forms both with Qt5 and Qt6. To only produce forms for a particular Qt version, please set the target accordingly.
